# tiss shortcuts — muscle-memory names for tiss commands
# Lives at ~/.config/tiss/shortcuts (create/open it with: tiss self shortcuts edit)
#
# One `name = command words` per line: the name becomes a real command
# (a shim on your PATH) that runs `tiss <command words>`. Uncomment a
# line to activate it, then run `tiss self shortcuts sync` (edit runs
# sync for you). Day to day, prefer:  tiss self shortcuts add NAME COMMAND...
#
# A suggested starter set:
# sd = saveData
# rd = readData
# lsData = lsData
# ts = time ts
# tfplan = tf plan
# encrypt = encrypt
# decrypt = decrypt
# tf = tf
# tfapply = tf apply
# tfshow = tf show
# saveData = saveData
# readData = readData
# cacheExec = cacheExec
# bkup = bkup
# ttmux = tmux go
